inn1.comm: starts off with a big wide down the leg side
back of a length, outside off, Watson shoulders arms to it
makes him play this time, on target, Watson responds with a back-foot defensive
goes for the expansive drive, one bounce to short cover
length delivery, around off, presses forward and defends it back to the bowler
looks to run this one down to third man, but the ball nips back a touch and cramps him
hands on heads all around as Watson gets an inside edge while looking to drive a fullish delivery, will get a single to long leg and keep strike
squares him straight away, back of a length, and Watson just plays inside the line, and is hit high on the back leg
length delivery, pushed back to the bowler
again playing inside the line, gets a leading edge, but safe and along the ground
this time he gets the inside edge, slightly shorter this one is and he looks to drive and gets the inside edge that travels safely to square leg
angling into the pads, pushed to square leg
this one grips from a length and gets him in the glove, good testing start from Gul - a maiden
angled across him,  he gets across and lets it go
fuller delivery, Marsh leans forward and pushes this one to cover
short, gives him the room, cuts, but straight to Fawad Alam at point
nicely bowled, pitches in front of middle, making him play, and it's just short of a length, and Marsh can't do much with it
this is a fuller delivery, guides it to wide of mid-on for a single
Watson is on his way, this time he gets the length and the width for his favourite horizontal-bat shot, and crashes it past point to the short square boundary
short of a length, around off, Marsh shoulders arms, 142ks
this is slightly wider and he lets it go without fuss
chops this one down to square of third man, and early and clear calling means they are back for the second before Rana Naveed can get the ball back in
slightly fuller, and he shoulders arms again
superb drive on the up, puts the front foot down, and meets the length delivery with a slightly open face, in the gap between mid-off and extra cover
looks to run this one down to third man, but it's too close to him
seam movement, in towards the batsman, can't do much else than playing it back
no room here as Watson looks to play it with an open face, good disciplined bowling
leans back this time and makes room, and dabs it down to third man
plays it with soft hands, picks out Mohammad Yousuf at mid-off, and pinches a single after hitting straight to the captain!
pick-up shot from in front of stumps, but Pakistan have the square-leg boundary covered
crashed through point, this is not that short, but Marsh goes ahead with the short-arm cut shot, this one doesn't deserve to go four, but goes racing past point
creating the pulling length with the short-arm pull, gets under this delivery just back of a length, and pulls it down the ground, and clears the infield with it
makes him bowl fuller, is expecting a fuller delivery, and Watson just murders it straight past him, all of Watson power there in this straight hit
pinches a couple now, gets behind the line and then opens the face, gets it past slip, and they rush back for two before Asif can get around from third man. Soft hands do the trick
gets a leading edge on the slower delivery while looking to flick it to leg, but he is safe
good bouncer, 139ks, tails in as he looks to pull, is late on the shot anyway
back of a length, cramping him, but he flicks it to left of mid-on and retains the strike
he has hit this really hard, gets down on a knee, opens up the arc, and off-drives, nay drills, it past mid-off. Not much wrong with the delivery here
cuts off the front foot, Alam gets a hand at point and keeps them down to one
no slips, and guided away through the region for a single
slight seam movement in towards him, hit hard and powerfully towards mid-on, but they come through for one because Yousuf is the fielder, who duly fumbles
angled across him, and allowed to go through to the keeper
superb delivery, lots of wrist in it, pitches around middle and leg, and seams away, beating Marsh just outside off
driven on the up, wide of mid-off, gets a single
presses forward and defends it towards cover
almost chopped on, looking for that same single to third man, gets a bottom edge that evades the stumps, and Akmal makes a nice diving one-handed save
same shot, this time he gets it right, and takes a single to third man
cut away but straight to third man this time
slightly outside off, angling away, and Marsh shoulders arms to it
gets the room, leans back, helps it through to third man
straight-drive, firm and powerful, but straight back to Asif, on the bounce
offcutter, pitches leg, heads towards middle, can't do much with it
another offcutter, slightly shorter too, and no room either, defended towards cover
gets cutting width with this one, but goes one bounce to Younis at cover-point
thick edge to this offcutter, gets a single to third man, good over
starts on target, just back of a length, on the stumps, played back to the bowler
a touch of width there, but can't get it past cover-point
short delivery, worked away to the left of square leg for a single
yorker, on the middle stump, can't do anything with this one
shorter, in the channel outside off, played to point
legcutter, looks to work it to leg, and it gets another leading edge from Watson, and it's safe again
short of a good length delivery and Marsh taps it away towards square leg
beauty! again short of a length and this one shaped away a touch from the off stump line, Marsh had no option but to play at it and he was beaten all ends up. Well bowled
on the middle and off stump line, played straight to the man at cover
short of a good length and this one is bit wide outside the off stump, Marsh leaves it through to the keeper
pitched  up and close to the off stump line, Marsh gets well forward and drives it straight to the fielder at mid-off
short of a good length delivery outside the off stump, Marsh stays back and taps it into the gap between the cover fielders and they scamper through for a well judged single
take that! good length delivery outside the off stump, nothing wrong but Marsh just steps forward and hits through the line and the ball sails away to the long-off fence. Clean hit
and again! similar length but bit wide outside the off stump and this time Marsh frees his arms and lofts it away to the wide long-off fence. Rana under pressure here
pitched up and thats driven straight bat, Rana gets a right-foot across and gets hit on the angle - no damage done though
forced away off the back-foot to the point region
played off the back-foot to backward point, early call and they scamper through for a single
short of a good length delivery on the middle and off stump line, defended watchfully
continues to keep it tight, back of a length, slight offcut away from the body, not much room
gets a touch too full and is flicked away through the gap between mid-on and midwicket, gets a comfortable three
offcutter again, Watson is looking at third man again, but it ends up too close to the body, Asif even gets into a stifled shout claiming pad-first
there's the slog, good and old fashioned, length ball, drags it from outside off and lofts it to cow corner
looks for the yorker, gets too straight, and is whipped away to square leg, they risk Salman Butt's arm and get a two thanks to the wide throw
this time the offcutter works, Watson premeditates another slog over midwicket, but Asif gets this perfectly right, pitches outside off, cuts back in, beats the waft, and hits the top of off
on target, back of a length, pitching within the stumps, ending up just outside off, defended
slightly straighter, and worked away for one
161 beats per minute as he goes back and across, and behind the line and defends
and again he gets across and defends to off

oh the impulsive pull gets him! sees something slightly short, and goes back and across to pull, but it's not quite short and beats him, and because it is slightly fuller than pulling length, it gives the impression that it stayed low. It might have too, but it looks worse than it did. Anyhow, hit dead in front and he has to go. The heart rate comes down to 146 beats per minute as he walks back
shoulders arms to a fullish delivery outside off
length ball, presses forward and defends towards mid-off
back to bowling offcutters, just back of a length, and not giving him much room
fuller and straighter, and worked away towards square leg, and Saeed Ajmal is slow, thus allowing them a couple
again, full and straight, and he has worked it away past midwicket this time, gets another couple
driven on the up, straight to mid-off, this time they don't risk it with Yousuf
runs this one past first slip, and gets a single to third man
plays with an open face, can't get it past point
this time he steers it past point, and gets a single
back of a length, just outside off, defended back to the bowler
comes forward, drives, connects well, can't get it past mid-on
stop-start after dropping it at his feet, they come through for the single, and Umar Akmal - running in from short cover - misses the stumps by a long way, Marsh was a goner had he hit
and again steers this one down towards third man for one
and beats him outside off right away, slight seam movement away from Marsh, enough to beat his attempt at steering it to third man
strays on the pads, and worked away to wide of square leg, will get two
across him, presses forward, and shoulders arms
gets an inside edge onto the pad as he looks to work it off his hips
pushes it down towards mid-off with soft hands and comes through for one - not without having to avoid a three-way collision: Clarke, marsh and Gul were all too close to each other for their liking
looks to drop and run but has hit too powerfully towards midwicket
flights this one outside off, driven down to long-off for one
full delivery outside off, and he gets back and across and lets it go through to the keeper
shouts of catch it, Clarke jumps out of the crease, the ball drifts and dips, he plays it in front of the body, but wide enough of Afridi
flat and fast and across him, played towards point
slower, googly, Marsh makes room, reads the googly, and cuts it in front of square, superb placement
overpitched on the pads, worked away for one
good line and length from Gul, just back of a length and no room to do anything with it
fuller, square-driven, gets it past point for a single
another run-out missed, again hit straight to cover by Clarke, they come through for one, Afridi goes for striker's end, and the throw is just a bit too high
fifty for Marsh, pulls this short delivery, and he gets a top edge fine of fine leg
this one he lets go through to Akmal outside off
strays too far down the leg side - just the second extra, the first one was the first delivery of the innings
angling across him and guided towards deep point for a single
wrong'un, and is driven to wide of long-off for two
on the pads, driven to long-on for one
presses forward, sees a short delivery, goes back, cuts it, gets a single
full, yorks him, hit back to the bowler
quicker delivery, chopped away to the right of short third for a single
dances down the wicket, flicks it off the pads for a single
length delivery, easily pushed down the ground for one
that cramping line and length, Marsh defends to the bowler
over-steps in this delivery, defended to cover
slower ball, mowed to deep midwicket, and they get two for it, hit just to wide of deep midwicket, Saeed Ajmal
this time Younis hits the stumps direct, but Marsh has been sent back this time, and he is safely in - horse has bolted and all that. Gets an overthrow to boot
slower ball, almost a yorker on the pads, can't do much with it
shorter, on the pads, and helped away for one
slightly short, Clarke goes back and cuts, gets a single to third man
beats him with a sharp offbreak, drawing him forward and then breaking away, Akmal sees him drag the back foot out, and whips the bails off, he has made it back by a split frame
drops it into the covers and comes through for a quick single
turned away off the pads, but straight to square leg
steps out of the crease, Ajmal shortens the length, hit to midwicket
premeditates the sweep, from outside off, gets a single to fine leg
helped away off the pads, gets a single to square leg
angling into the pads, can't get it past midwicket
slower ball, turns out to be a fulltoss on the pads, Gul fumbles at fine leg, another couple ensues
another couple to fine leg, this is worked to the left of Gul, but it's also soft hands that means Gul has to run in too, and he isn't quick enough in doing so
this one straightens a touch, and Clarke has to check his attempt at working it away to leg
goes back and across, and guides it to the right of point for one
Clarke dances down to the pitch of the ball, and drives him down to long-off
gets an inside edge onto the pads as he looks to turn it to leg
premeditates another sweep, misses this time
tossed up wider, driven square, can't beat cover-point
goes across this time, and works it from outside off towards square leg
jumps out of the crease again, gets a leading edge this time, all along the ground towards cover
low fulltoss, hit straight to midwicket
offcutter, an obvious one, helped away to short third, and Gul lets it through his arms, poor fielding
tries another offcutter, goes horribly wrong, long hop, outside leg, and pulled away easily for four
goes for the cut, there is extra bounce, goes uppishly, but past point
short and wide, cut away for one
regulation legbreak, flighted, on the pads, knocked around for one
Ajmal draws him wide, flighting it outside off, pushed in front of his body, towards cover
shapes to sweep, Ajmal bowls it in flat, little cat and mouse going on here
opens the face this time, but hits straight to short third
flighted outside off, defended towards point
this time he connects with the sweep, all along the ground, gets off strike
topspinner, Clarke goes back and cuts it for one
nicely bowled, a quick leg break, around off, defended to cover
quicker one, going with the arm, gets the inside half of the bat, fine of fine leg
comes down the track, bunts it to wide of midwicket
flighted on the pads, hit straight towards midwicket
pushed to cover and before Fawad turns and throws they have made it for an easy single
comes down the track and drives down the ground for one
again he uses his feet to get to the pitch of it, and drives it to long-on
looks to sweep, again, flatter delivery comes out, he misses, but has got his pad outside the line
shapes to sweep, Ajmal goes wide, he aborts the shot, opens the face, but can't get it past short third
cover-drive, Younis makes a nice diving save at extra cover
shorter, opens the face, straight to Afridi at cover-point
sweeps from outside off, all along the ground again, and gets a single
he follows the Clarke method this time, coming out of the crease and driving it down the ground
shorter and flatter, 101ks, Clarke goes for the cut, but it's not that short, and is beaten
steps out and gets a single to long-on again
stays back and pushes this shortish delivery to long-on
again Clarke steps out, this one goes straight with the arm, but he still gets a single off the inside half of the bat
fulltoss on the pads, worked away for a single
flat delivery, worked away from outside off to a vacant midwicket for one
this time the offbreak beats him, but Clarke's pads are covering it in case he steps out and misses
draws him wide this time, Clarke pushes at away from his body, gets an inside edge, and still gets a single
steps out, gets to the pitch of it, wristily flicks it to wide of long-on, and they take a couple to Gul
bunted away towards midwicket for a single
doosra, almost beats a stepping-out Clarke, but he manages an outside edge and a single to a fumbling Asif at short third
nothing can keep him in the crease, though, he dances down again, and gets a single to long-on
offbreak, clear change of grip, pitches leg, beats him outside off
another offbreak, this time he cuts, but can't get it past backward point
this time it's cut to the left of point, gets a single
regulation legbreak, goes back and punches it past cover
offbreak, outside leg, turning towards the stumps, Marsh misses out on an easy single
and he steps down the track again and gets a single to long-on
looks for the cut, the ball follows him, but he manages to open the face and get a single to point
sharp offbreak, worked away off the pads, gets a single to midwicket
looks for the extra-cover drive, the ball goes straight through and cramps the shot
quicker delivery, just outside off, defended to cover

superb bowling, follows that quicker delivery with a nicely flighted, inviting offbreak outside off, Marsh is drawn out of the crease, as if pulled by a string, and then the ball bounces away from his reach and spins away, beating him, and Taufel doesn't even need to go to the third umpire
flat and fast, into the pads, Clarke misses out
quick footwork again, but can't get it wide enough of Afridi
bunts this one to left of cover for one
nice legbreak on target, White comes forward and defends
again a nice flighted legbreak outside off, 88ks, defended to cover
this is flatter and quicker, 98ks, but just as accurate and is defended
Clarke comes down the track again, and gets a single to fine leg as this is fired down the pads
flat offbreak, 94ks, worked to square leg
this one jumps at him, the toppie, but he gets a single off the glove
dropped, Ajmal has bowled beautifully again, Clarke is stepping out, but he makes him play away from the body, Yousuf at short cover dives, gets a hand to it , but can't hold on to it
flat and straight, defended
big, premeditated sweep, misses but gets his front pad outside off
short and flat,. late-cut, can't get it past short third
gets a single down the ground this time
presses forward and pushed down the ground for one, one would expect the mid-off up
driven to cover, can't find the gap
googly this time, beats him, but is going down the leg side
and he comes down the track, and works it away for his 29th single out of a score of 35
starts with a length ball outside off, punched away for one
looks to drive on the up, the ball stops on him a touch, goes uppishly down the ground, this time, though, mid-off is up to stop the single
punched away to sweeper-cover, gets a single
back of a length, pushed down the ground, gets a single to long-on
drops it towards cover with soft hands, and calls early, and gets a single
back of a length, angling towards the pads, and worked away for one
flat outside off, cuts, can't beat cover-point
presses forward again, but Afridi slips in the quicker one, catches him on the crease, big shout for lbw, but Taufel reckons it's going down with the angle
cut to short third, gets a dicey single, Rana fumbles
what a shot, casually done, makes room, gets under the legbreak and goes inside-out, clean over extra cover
appeal for catch down the leg side, no signal from the umpire, must have clicked the thigh pad
short and wide and cut away for one
front-foot pull, looks to push him back in the crease, but it's not sharp enough, and he pulls it wide of midwicket
shoulders arms outside off
offcutter, comes forward and works it wide of midwicket for one
drives away from the body gets an inside edge onto the pads, wants a single but is sent back, Afridi from covers throws wildly, it goes over the middle of the pitch
another inside edge, for White this time, it rolls off towards square leg and he gets another single
another offcutter, on the pads, worked away for single to midwicket
short, outside off, pushed away to sweeper-cover
short again, cut away powerfully, gets a single
Clarke dances down the wicket, bunts this one towards square, knows he has hit it softly and comes back for two
comes down the track again, pushes this one down to long-on
googly, quicker bowl too, deflected off the pads, nice shot, fine leg is too square
shorter, outside off, pushed down the ground, walks down for a single, Afridi's 10 overs done for 55 runs
nice quick offbreak, no room, pushed back to the bowler
this one turns into the pads, hit down the ground for one
Clarke dances right down to the pitch of this one, and takes a single to long-on
doosra, goes back in the crease, and cuts it to deep point
beautifully bowled again, big turn, flat delivery too, beats the poke, but he gets a leg-bye
short outside off, cut away towards sweeper-cover
walks down the track, Rana bowls short, and he plays it with soft hands towards third man and gets a couple
slower ball, he is early into the shot, has to check, can't beat the straightish midwicket
driven powerfully, but straight to cover
another good-looking drive on the up, another dot ball, because he can't get it past point
slower offcutter, worked away off the pads, past short fine, runs three, runs all the way to a hard-earned fifty - no boundaries in it
another run-out missed, bunted straight to point and runs through, Younis would have got White had it hit down the stumps at the non-striker's end, but misses
quick offbreak on the pads, hit straight to midwicket
slog-swept, slog-swept hard, one bounce to deep midwicket
runs this one down to third man, hands over the strike to White
doosra, leading edge, lobs wide of him, the single brings up Australia's 200
another doosra, another leading edge, but this is all along the ground, to long-off
shorter, spinning in, punched through covers
again Clarke drives Rana straight to cover
walks down the ground, pushes it past the outstretched arm of Rana, and calls early for two because he hasn't hit it too hard, and he comes back for two
steers it down to third man for a single

lovely legcutter, yanks the wrist at the point of delivery, pitches off, back of a length, moves away a touch, squares him up, takes the outside edge, and White has to go - this should delay the Powerplay further
full delivery, driven straight down to mid-off
looks for the dab to third man, can't beat point
driven on the up, Clarke's first boundary, thanks to a misfield by Butt at cover, lets it go under his knees
walks across and flicks it over short fine, superb shot, superb awareness of the field setting
bunted to cover for a single, and rightly Butt has been removed from there, and Umar Akmal brought in
back of a length, dropped towards point, and comes through for one, quick, decisive running
walks down the pitch, drives down the ground, gets a single to long-on
short and wide, cut away to sweeper-cover for a single
short, and short-arm-pulled to wide of fine leg, gets two
flat delivery again, cut away, Umar Akmal fumbles, but they decide against the single
one flat delivery too many, he waits for it, delays the previous shot a touch, and gets left enough of point, smart shot
premeditated sweep, but what a connection! He is expecting a slower offbreak, and shapes up for the sweep, gets right on top of it, and bisects the two fielders in the deep
crunchy drive this time, can't get past Younis at extra cover
looks for another late cut, finds Akmal at point
length ball, driven powerfully, making room, hits straight to extra cover
slower ball, worked away off the pads, wide of deep square leg, gets two
looks to walk across and go over midwicket, Gul drops it in short and misdirects down the leg side, and it bounces in front of Kamran and gets him in the neck
the field is set for the yorker, but this is the low fulltoss, Hussey gets under it and deposits it into the midwicket fence
slower ball, looks to slog this from outside off to midwicket, gets an inside edge to short fine
yorker gone wrong again, this time on the shorter side, so he can't quite get under it, and gets a single to Yousuf at midwicket
full, slightly short of the perfect yorker, and he hits it to wide of long-on and comes back for two
pushed to the left of midwicket, gets a single
low fultoss, gets it straighter of long-off and takes two
good yorker, just down the leg side, and moving away after pitching, Akmal does well to prevent any more extras
good shot, gooood shot, shimmies down the track, check-drives this length delivery past extra cover
gets the yorker right this time, hit back to the bowler
just short of being a yorker, and he plays the short-arm flick square on the on side, Butt runs hard and knocks it back into field of play, saves one run
slower short delivery, swiped towards midwicket, will get a single
makes room, follows him, turns out to be a leg-side half-volley, and is worked away without fuss, square leg can't do much about it
good bouncer, gets the top edge, but it's a no-ball, and Clarke pushes for two: he wants the free hit
high fulltoss, wide of off, called no-ball for height, swings and misses, gets a bye as it bounces in front of Akmal

interesting, Taufel from square leg calls a no-ball, not enough men in the circle? swipes, gets it past short fine, and gets two, comedy of errors for Pakistan. Free-hit continues - there were four men outside the circle. It's all happening!
good yorker, will get just a single to deep square leg
drags it from outside off, bat turns it in his hand, gets a single to midwicket
nice juicy fulltoss, and bang it's in the crowd behind the midwicket fence
slower ball, he gets under it, over midwicket, Umar Akmal does well, running around from long-on and keeping them to two
length ball, driven inside-out, but doesn't get it wide enough of long-off, and retains strike
slower ball, swept square of deep square leg, gets a couple
fulltoss, sliced away off the face of the bat, through cover, mis-hit, but the fulltoss deserves to go for four
fuller, this time they have a sweeper-cover back, will get only a single
well bowled, full and wide of off, away from Clarke's reach
good yorker, just outside off, played with an open face, gets a single to point
a near-yorker, driven to wide of long-off, gets a couple
yorker, just a single to point, can he bowl five more of those?
well bowled, slower delivery, yet a yorker, beats him outside off
Hussey misses 50, looks to walk down the pitch to alter the length, gets too much under a low fulltoss, and they have protection down at long-off where Younis makes no mistake

he is on a hat-trick, would you believe it? Last over he bowled three back-to-back no-balls, and here he has both the settled batsmen in two deliveries. Clarke walks across, looking to hit it over leg, gets an inside edge on a near-yorker, is castled
good wide yorker, Hauritz misses, Haddins is backing up a long way, and comes through for a bye. Akmal hits the stumps direct, but Haddin has beaten him by a split frame
Haddin looks for a scoop over fine leg, Gul is fast and wide of off, and Haddin just makes a limp connection and gets a single

inn2.comm: starts off with a full delivery, on the pads, driven down to mid-on
low fulltoss on the pads, Butt accepts the gift, clips it to the square-leg boundary
angling into the pads, no swing, flicked away, can't get it past the square leg in the circle
gets it closer to off stump this time, defended with a straight bat
this one kicks off a length, 140ks, beats Butt who is almost drawn onto the front foot, and goes chest high to Haddin
full and wide, gives Butt space to swing his arms, and out comes a gorgeous cover-drive that finds the gap
back of a length, into the pads, worked to wide of mid-on
and a nice nice shot here, the punch-drive from Butt, angled across him and hit on the up, wide of mid-off
angled across him again, this time he shoulders arms
shorter this time, closer to off stump, presses forward and defends
another punch-drive, inside-out, past short cover, gets a single because White dives and slows it down

given! Akmal moves across to work it to the leg, misses it completely, Harris goes for the shout right away. Asoka de Silva upholds it. Replays show the ball kissing the top of off, and possibly hitting him outside the line. There were two sounds, but definitely no inside edge
on target, no room, not straight enough to work it to leg
steers this one down to third man for a single
short ball, angled across him, defended solidly
goes back and across and defends to cover
plays away from the body this time, gets an inside edge onto the pads
leaves this one alone outside off
driven firmly, towards mid-off
hit on the up again, gets it past short cover, not much power in it, but will get a single
looks to drop and run, but Clarke at cover is alert
back of a length, on off, no room, defended to cover
again stays around off, just short of good length, defended towards cover
slightly fuller, Younis comes forward, and defends towards point
hurried into the pull shot, but gets enough bat on it, Hauritz at mid-on gets a hand to it while diving, and saves one run for the team
driven away from the body, hit two bounce to cover
still not off the mark, goes back and across and punches it towards cover
slower ball, 133ks, pushed, smack off the middle of the bat, but straight ti mid-off, another loud "No" call from Younis
bouncer now, too short, Younis has enough time to duck under it
another solid drive straight to hand, a fumble at short cover but Butt sends him back - rightly
punched down the ground, straight to mid-off
slashes outside off, gets a single to third man
length ball, around off, driven down to mid-off, still not off the mark
slightly slower, presses forward and defends outside off
defends right under his head, not taking Harris on
drives in front of his body, connects nicely, but straight on the bounce to short cover
squares him up, lbw appeal right away, pitched outside leg
squares him up again, although it's going straight with the angle, thick outside edge towards point
back of a length, angled across, hit on the bounce to short cover
short of good length, just around off, gets close to the stumps, not much of an angle, defended back to the bowler
nice shot, gets a touch of width, and eased away through point, cut shot without power, just guides it
too straight, helped away past square leg, again just looks for the placement rather than power
length ball, around off, Younis gets on the front foot, and pushes it down to mid-off
shorter, gets it to rise high, and defended again
finally off the mark, driven with an open face, Ponting dives at backward point, gets a hand on it, keeps them down to one
surprise bouncer, Butt ducks under it
angled across him, defended towards point
shot! flick-pull, short into the body, the pace is not disconcerting, and Butt stands tall and dismisses it
this one goes through the field, superb timing, just a push outside off, off the back foot, beats short cover and it flies across the outfield
similar shot, but this time he finds Hussey at short cover
slower ball, is early into his attempted dab to third man
drives a length ball, straight down to mid-off
slower ball, pushed one bounce to Hussey at short cover
short and wide, and Younis gets on top of it and cuts it between Ponting and Clarke at backward point and cover-point respectively. Watson is left admonishing himself
back of a length, not much room, defended off the back foot
on the pads, worked away to wide of deep square leg, gets a couple
length ball around off, defended
just short of a length, around middle and off, defended towards cover
fuller, presses forward and defends it towards mid-off
gets a hint of room here, and runs this down to third man
length ball, around middle, worked towards midwicket
slower ball, drops it towards cover and runs through for a well-judged single
dabs this one down to third man
angled across him, shapes to drive, but changes his mind, and lets Haddin earn his living
runs this one down to third man, from in front of off stump
driven on the up, uppish, but wide enough of White at cover, Hussey from sweeper-cover makes a diving save, and they take only two
starts with a length delivery, around off, Butt gets an inside edge towards mid-on
on target again, pushed down to mid-off

Asoka has struck again, no movement, going with angle, headed towards middle stump, and it had to be pitched outside leg. Asoka de Silva doesn't think so, and raises his finger. It's pitched way outside leg. What's more? It's going over the stumps. Salman Butt is furious as he walks off. No show of dissent at the wicket, though
defended off the back foot, towards leg
and going with those shiny pads, Yousuf starts off with a sparkling lofted shot, steps down the wicket and smashes it back over McKay's head
straying down the pads, and helped away fine. Fine leg is too square, and they come back for three
looks to come forward, Watson bowls short, keeps him on the crease as he defends
superb touch cricket, slower ball, into the pads, and glanced away fine, no chance for the fielder. Forget Yousuf's fielding and captaincy, when he bats he is something else
looks for the dab to third man, gets an inside edge onto the pad
again he looks for third man, again he gets an inside edge onto the pads

like they say in the Caribbean, after one time is two times! he looks to run it down to third man again, and this is the third inside edge he gets, this time the pad doesn't come around in time to save him
gets a thick edge to one that stays low a touch, goes fine of third man, gets a couple
looks to force this one through cover, doesn't get close to it, the inside half of the bat takes it to mid-on
back of a length, outside off, played towards point

that's a beast of a delivery to get on a slow pitch, digs it in short, Younis thinks he is safely swaying away, but it chases him all the way back, and kisses the bat on the way. Haddin takes a nice overhead catch, one-handed, full stretch, lovely to watch
starts off with the shuffle, defends just outside off
fuller delivery, outside off, played towards point
length delivery, around off, defended back to the bowler
angled across Umar, shoulders arms
moves across, and works him to wide of square leg for two
fuller delivery, driven down to mid-off
bouncer, too high, easily ducks under it
aggressive delivery, 143ks, back of a length, rising towards the chest, defended well
stays back of a length, defended off the back foot
runs this one down to third man and keeps the strike
goes for the bouncer, angled down the leg side, was good when it passed the stumps
stays on the crease, and defends a length ball
good running, guides it to slightly fine of third man, and comes back for two
opens the face again, but hits it straight to third man this time
just outside off, defended to cover
back of a length, around off, defended back to the bowler
full delivery, square-driven, straight to cover-point
nearly played on, looks to defend outside off, the inside edge goes wide of leg stump
beauty! 144ks, back of a length, seaming away, Umar is tentative, misses the edge not by much
looks to open the face on a full delivery, can't get it past point
back of a length again, hops and defends
soft hands, plays towards point, and retains the strike
turn there but Umar nudges it late, past short third
turning into the pads, helped around the corner for one
comes forward, opens the face, plays towards point
angled into the pads, and played for an easy single to get off the mark
looks to turn it to leg, it's the toppie, gets the leading edge, but it's safe
this is too short, and worked away for an easy single to square leg
starts back of a length, defended towards midwicket
looks to guide it to third man, doesn't get close to the line, and is also beaten by the pace
takes a quick single to cover, drop-and-run really
pitched outside leg, angling away, defended towards cover
another drop and run, towards mid-off this time
short delivery, gets big on him, fended from in front of his face, keeps it down, though, and gets a single too
another nice nudge past short third man, almost out of Haddin's gloves, too wide and short
gets forward, to the pitch of it, with soft hands he works it to square leg, calls early, and runs fast to get two
slightly shorter, not too short, defended to midwicket
looks to drop and run to cover, but Haddin is out of the blocks in a jiffy
spinning into the pads and worked around the corner for one
leading edge as he looks to turn it to leg, all along the ground, though
angling towards the off stump, looks for a single to point, but has hit too powerfully
chops it down to third man, wants two but it has gone straight to Watson
shuffles all the way across, finds it is on the pads, and gets a single to square leg
slower ball, 124 ks, and Umar is beaten while trying to run it down to third man. There is a little noise as it passes the bat, no appeal, though
digs this one in short, down the leg side
dabs it towards cover-point and comes through for one
edged, and just past the diving Haddin, flirting with one that is far from him, and Harris - big unit that he is - makes a superb diving save at the third man boundary
short, cut away past backward point
presses forward, guides it past point and takes a single
top-edges a sweep, from way outside off, lands safe
turn, angled in, pitches, moves away, defended towards point
flighted around off, defended towards point
getting consistent turn now, defended off the back foot
nice shot, angling into the pads, a touch too far down, and he smartly deflects it fine of fine leg
is drawn into a loose shot now, wide, there for being cut, but the feet don't move, and is beaten
back of a length, just outside off, defended towards cover
leaves this one alone outside off
fishes outside the line of off, no feet again, and is lucky not to have edged it
gets back and across this time and cuts it to sweeper-cover
the overspinner, hurries on to Umar, defended to leg
paddles from outside off, and hares between the wickets to come back for two
another overspinner, defended back to the bowler
arm ball this time, just straying down the pads
sharp turn from outside off, Umar tries to cut, but it is not that short
flighted outside off, Umar presses forward and defends
defended off the front foot, towards cover
nicely placed, punched off the back foot, between cover and extra cover, gets two
fuller, on the stumps, gets him in a semi-tangle because of the shuffle, worked to midwicket eventually
cut powerfully, one bounce to cover-point
offcutter, angling towards off, Alam wants one to cover-point, Akmal sends him back
shoulders arms to this one
topspinner, played towards short fine
turn and bounce, but he gets on top of the bounce and cuts it along the ground
sweeps, sweeps well, but finds White at square leg
short, looks to turn it around the corner, can't beat backward square leg
pulls, it's not that short, hence it goes in front of square
full, driven to short cover
short, into the pads, misses, the ball rolls along off the pad, and Alam calls him through for a single
driven on the up, Clarke dives at extra cover and gets a hand onto it, saving two runs
short, punched away, Marsh at cover fumbles
comes forward and defends towards cover
looks to press forward and is bounced, somehow he gets the bat in the way and manages to keep the pull shot down
punched to the right of Bollinger at mid-off and they come through for a single
driven off the back foot, gets a single to sweeper-cover
superb slog sweep, flat delivery, full, in his arc, and he connects well, and clears midwicket with ease
having shortened his length, he cuts him this time, slightly late, so that he goes square of sweeper-cover, and takes two
reverse-sweep this time, from outside off, and gets it past short third
gets a stride in, and drops and runs for a single
misjudges the length, pushes forward, and then goes back to defend
moves across the stumps, and works it to deep square leg for a single
pulled away off the front foot, powerful slap of a shot, over  midwicket
another drop and run, they don't look like subcontinental batsmen - they have run as well as, say, Dhoni and Raina when batting together
flicked in the air, doesn't get enough power, and good for him, because it almost carries to Marsh at deep square leg
angled a long way across him, called a wide
presses forward, defends it back to the bowler
pierces the cover ring with a punch, but there is sweeper-cover in place
slow, teasing him, Alam shuffles, then makes room, and goes for the pull, and still is early into the shot, the ball bounces just over the off stump
Ponting dives full length at cover, they still come through for one
worked away from in front of the stumps, and they hare up and down and get a couple
fifty for Umar, what a busy little hustle this has been, gets there with a late cut past backward point, does the sajda, well done Umar
full delivery, driven down the ground, gets a single
beats Fawad with the sharp offbreak, angled into him, then turning away
Umar goes for the pull, mistimes it, and it bounces short of Watson at mid-on
this is better, he gets across, and wafts it, nay belts it, all along the carpet, but through the leg-side field, mid-off already back to long-on
looks to turn it down to leg, but it is a touch too sharp and hits him in the thigh
fuller outside off, opens the face, gets a single to third man
gets an inside edge while driving, goes to the left hand of Clarke at midwicket, hits the stumps direct but Alam is in
makes room, runs this down to third man, gets a single
cut from in front of stumps, can't get it past point
looks to cut a half-volley, and is duly beaten
looks to cut again, not that short, gets the top edge, one bounce to Watson at short third
he is hell bent at cutting, again from in front of middle and leg, too full too, doesn't get anything
flighted on the pads, worked away for a single to square leg
and he drops and runs, it's not even gone off the square but they come through conmfortably
cut away, gets a single to deep point
his penchant for the late-cut gets him, looks to manufacture a single, Harris is too close to his body - in fact it nips back in - and gets the outside edge
back of a length, defends it to point
seams in again, gets a leg-bye
presses forward, takes a single to point
big back lift, Harris is accurate, Afridi defends it back
short, punched away to sweeper-cover
not looking for the six here, paddles it smartly for a single
punched away, can't get it past Ponting at short cover
drives this one straight to point
paddles this one away, and takes a couple
flat, on the pads, hit straight to midwicket
Afridi goes, goes over mid-off, gets three, smart shot, not looking for too much power, just clears the infield
full, on the pads, flicked away, gets a single
goes for the big hit outside off, doesn't beat extra cover
slower ball, goes cross-batted, gets just over midwicket, wide long-on cuts it off
takes a sharp single, just to the right of cover
slower ball, runs it down to third man, takes a single
pulls him right away, flat and aerial, one bounce to deep square leg
White fumbles at cover, Alam is alert, and they come through for the single
back of a length, angled across him, cuts it to third man for a single
full ball, driven, this time White is alert at cover
slower ball, guides it past point for a single
pulls off the front foot, gets the top half of the bat, but finds the gap between deep square leg and deep midwicket
full ball, hit straight to Clarke at midwicket
dragged from outside off, gets a single down to long-on
full and fast, driven to sweeper-cover for a single

and finally his shuffle is breached, the shuffle always leaves him exposed to a sharp incoming delivery, and perhaps for the first time tonight, Australia bowl one such delivery to Fawad, and the inside edge cannons into the middle stump
is late into the pull shot, almost an afterthought, is beaten by a long way
fuller delivery, driven with an open face, gets a single
full and straight, played towards point
slashes outside off, misses
bunts it to cover and takes a single
moves across, back of a length delivery, drops it at his feet and runs through
pulls all over a short delivery, lucky to survive
makes room and runs it down to third man for a single
cut away wide of third man, this shot would have done Watson proud
this cut goes straight to third man - right so Watson to Afridi, Air Time?
wide delivery outside off, looks to open the face, misses
slower ball, driven to extra cover
drives a length ball down the ground for a single
back of a length, they pinch a single off the inside edge
short delivery, helped away past point, hands over the strike to Afridi
makes room, Bollinger fires a nice yorker, outside off, gets some bat to it, and takes a single to backward point
short delivery again, runs it down to third man
slower ball, 126ks, and he has drilled it through White at midwicket, pulled away so powerfully that the fielder doesn't want to get in line
fulltoss outside off, slashes inside the line
full and straight, driven down to long-of for one
starts with a slower ball, Afridi backs away, and powers it over point, good start for Pakistan
back of a length this time, quick too, pushed down the ground for one
Rana steps down, lofts this length delivery straight, gets a couple before long-on can come around
runs this one down to short third and takes a single
moves around in the crease, first across, then away, Watson bowls short, and he has punched away absolutely sweetly, all along the ground, through point
Watson comes, Watson goes, backs away, gets a length delivery, gets under it, inside-out, over extra cover, straight into the debris where reconstruction is going on - 18 off the over
drilled towards extra cover, Ponting gets a bad bounce, Rana doesn't come through for one
full and straight, hit back at Harris, who stretches out his left hand and keeps it to dot
steps out of the crease, and gets a single to long-on
yorker, well bowled, Afridi can get just a single
fulltoss, hit down the ground, straight, "Do Lala do" is the call right away. Do meaning two, and Lala being how Pakistan players address Afridi. And they come back for two
what a shot, stands his ground, gets a length ball outside , and smack he goes over extra cover. Game on here
low fulltoss, hit hard, straight to mid-off
full and straight, Afridi makes room and swings, gets a thick edge to third man for a single
good slower ball, Rana almost plays two shots to it, and misses, 106ks, he is a very good operator with that slower ball
makes room, McKay follows him with a sharp delivery, Rana comes back for two leg-byes to third man
ho ho ho Rana has well and truly joined the party, clears the front leg, gets a length delivery, gets under it, swings clean as a whistle, and clears cow corner
slower ball, beats him, goes off the thigh, bounces in front of Haddin, the deflection of the keeper beats short fine leg, and they hustle back for two
whoa! Afridi moves all the way across, takes a low fulltoss, and gets into an awkward position, and gets it past short fine leg
Harris has roared right back! Perfect delivery, yorker, landing on the crease on front of middle, and squeezes under Afridi's bat. What a ripper!
sharp bouncer, Gul has no clue about it
No. 4 for Harris, Gul just throws his bat at this length ball, gets under it, and it goes up perpendicularly, Haddin gets under it and takes a nice catch despite the swirl
Rana swipes, can't get it past midwicket
lovely shot, makes room, not much room with this full delivery, but squeezes it through the covers, all along the ground
short ball, tucks him up, can't get it off the square
just meets that ball with an open face, gets it off the middle of the bat, beats cover, and gets four, just like that

double miss here! It's actually funny! short ball, hit straight to White at midwicket, White goes for the underarm flick, misses, Ponting - backing up - still has Ajmal short, but misses from a metre. White sees the funny side of things, but he is covering his face while laughing. Don't want to cross the boss
slower ball, gives it his all, the top edge lands short of third man
lbw appeal, but headed down the leg side, will get a leg-bye
turns a shortish delivery around the corner, keeps the strike
and Harris gets five, Rana is going for everything, doesn't connect well, and lobs it to midwicket. Harris delighted, what an effort this has been
gets behind this full delivery and defends
short ball, fends, misses
full on the pads, worked away for a single
angled down the pads, and he gets four leg-byes
worked away off the pads for a single. Well bowled Ryan Harris, coming in for Peter Siddle who tormented Pakistan two days ago, and taking a five-for
angled across Ajmal, who shoulders arms
yorker outside off, Ajmal misses
runs it down to third man for a single
fulltoss, hit down the ground to mid-off
backs away, almost plays this one on
gets right behind the line and defends
slog-sweeps, one bounce to deep midwicket
flatter delivery, stops and turns, defended to leg
looks to slog, misses
that's the series for Australia. 3-0! Asif top-edges when looking slog, and Haddin is not letting anybody else take it
